01:00:55,811 --> 01:00:58,352
So I come from Nepal, Mount Everest country.

601
01:00:59,232 --> 01:01:06,956
The day before yesterday, there was a big earthquake in Nepal and many people died and many houses collapsed.

602
01:01:08,297 --> 01:01:17,461
Is our commission has jurisdiction to express some statement about their impactful life?

603
01:01:20,650 --> 01:01:25,412
So the commission's jurisdiction is written in by ordinance.

604
01:01:25,652 --> 01:01:37,557
And right now, my sense is the commission is reframing itself and using the broad lens of human rights.

605
01:01:38,238 --> 01:01:46,221
I've not seen the commission reach the stage of making statements for individual incidents that occur.

606
01:01:46,781 --> 01:01:50,243
Because whilst I believe that we can all agree

607
01:01:51,217 --> 01:01:51,798
On here.

608
01:01:52,478 --> 01:02:01,926
There are unfortunately so many horrible things that are happening that I would hate to miss something inadvertently.

609
01:02:02,987 --> 01:02:09,852
So, you know, if you if your question is, can the commission, make a statement about the.

610
01:02:11,697 --> 01:02:23,766
earthquake that occurred in Nepal, I would have to open that up to the commissioners and I would have to really see if that is something that is in line with the ordinance.

611
01:02:26,929 --> 01:02:28,890
I for one would like to have that conversation.

612
01:02:29,011 --> 01:02:37,097
I think it's an interesting point, particularly if some of these things affect a population that is, you know, invested in

613
01:02:37,920 --> 01:02:41,985
in our city, it seems as though we should, I think we should have the conversation.

614
01:02:42,025 --> 01:02:43,367
I think it would be very interesting.

615
01:02:45,072 --> 01:02:49,495
I think that, you know, what I will say is I can't say have the conversation.

616
01:02:49,675 --> 01:02:52,117
I can't say don't have the conversation.

617
01:02:52,577 --> 01:03:02,525
But what I will say is that if you have the conversation for one, you must be willing to have the conversation for all.

618
01:03:03,125 --> 01:03:08,509
Under no circumstances can we not have that conversation for all.

619
01:03:09,069 --> 01:03:12,712
So this is something that I ask that you search

620
01:03:14,755 --> 01:03:17,043
and you think deeply about.

621
01:03:18,086 --> 01:03:20,775
And I say that as somebody who is

622
01:03:21,732 --> 01:03:26,915
used to working from the unpopular side, right?

623
01:03:27,055 --> 01:03:35,600
So, you know, many, many moons ago, when I was doing more clinical services, right?

624
01:03:36,260 --> 01:03:45,325
I, yes, you know, I worked with survivors, but my true work was with the batterers, you know, not the popular side.

625
01:03:46,422 --> 01:03:52,927
So, I raised that because as a human rights commission for a city.

626
01:03:53,668 --> 01:04:05,738
We need to make sure that everyone feels comfortable coming to us, and we cannot allow ourselves to inadvertently become politicized.

627
01:04:06,539 --> 01:04:08,060
